HEADWORD: disoriented
<hw>disoriented</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having lost one's
bearings physically or mentally.</def> <illu>I frequently find myself
<ex>disoriented</ex> when I come up out of the subway</illu>;<illu>the
anesthetic left her completely <ex>disoriented</ex></illu>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> confused, lost.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>socially disoriented; withdrawn from social
interactions.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> alienated, anomic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>disorienting</ent>⟦br⟧
